<div class="docs-section">
  <h2 class="docs-section__title">Dark Hero</h2>
  <p class="docs-section__description">Use as the primary page header for landing pages, campaign pages, and section introductions where a strong first impression is needed. The dark background with inverted type creates clear contrast and draws focus to the headline and CTA. Add a background image or video via <code>.hero__bg</code> to further reinforce the message.</p>
  <div class="ds-preview" style="padding: 0; overflow: hidden;">
    <section class="hero hero--dark" style="min-height: 360px;">
      <div class="hero__content">
        <span class="hero__eyebrow">Open Days</span>
        <h1 class="hero__title" style="font-size: var(--text-display-m);">Discover Your Future</h1>
        <p class="hero__subtitle">Join us in the heart of London's Regent's Park.</p>
        <div class="hero__actions">
          <a href="#" class="btn btn--primary-inverted">Book Your Place</a>
          <a href="#" class="btn btn--secondary-inverted">View Courses</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="docs-section">
  <h2 class="docs-section__title">Editorial (Gradient) Hero</h2>
  <p class="docs-section__description">Use for brand campaign pages, news features, or editorial content where a photographic background would feel too heavy. The zingy-yellow-to-green gradient is distinctly Regent's and works well when the content itself needs to be the hero — no supporting imagery required. Keep the headline short and impactful.</p>
  <div class="ds-preview" style="padding: 0; overflow: hidden;">
    <section class="hero hero--editorial" style="min-height: 300px;">
      <div class="hero__content">
        <span class="hero__eyebrow" style="color: var(--color-charcoal);">Campaign</span>
        <h1 class="hero__title" style="color: var(--color-charcoal); font-size: var(--text-display-m);">Where Ambition Meets Opportunity</h1>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</div>
